# Git commit authorship (whyDPI)

This repository has **one human maintainer on GitHub**: `byrdltd`.
The public Contributors graph must stay that way.

## Hard rules for agents and automation

1. **Never** append `Co-authored-by:` trailers — especially
   `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`. Cursor's IDE
   integration injects this when using plain `git commit`; it pollutes
   the GitHub Contributors page permanently.
2. **Author and committer** must always be:
   `byrdltd <byrdltd@users.noreply.github.com>`.
3. **Do not** use `git commit --amend` for commits that may have been
   created through Cursor's commit path if a co-author trailer might
   reappear — verify with `git log -1 --format=%B`.
4. When the user asks for commits and co-author injection is a risk,
   build the commit with **`git commit-tree`** instead of `git commit`:

   ```bash
   export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME='byrdltd'
   export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL='byrdltd@users.noreply.github.com'
   export GIT_COMMITTER_NAME='byrdltd'
   export GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL='byrdltd@users.noreply.github.com'
   TREE=$(git write-tree)
   PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD)   # omit -p for root commit
   git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" -F /path/to/msg.txt
   git reset --hard <new-sha>
   ```

5. After every commit, **verify** before push:

   ```bash
   git log -1 --format='%B' | grep -iE 'co-authored-by|cursoragent' && echo BAD || echo OK
   ```

6. Release automation (Scoop manifest, AUR checksums) commits as
   **byrdltd**, never `whydpi-release-bot` or `github-actions[bot]`
   on `main`.

## Hooks

Local guards live in `.githooks/commit-msg` and
`scripts/reject-cursor-coauthor.sh`. Enable once per clone:

```bash
git config core.hooksPath .githooks
# or: pre-commit install --hook-type commit-msg
```
